<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:The_Kop,_Anfield.jpg" class="image"><img alt="The end of a football stadium with th seats painted red." src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/The_Kop,_Anfield.jpg/300px-The_Kop,_Anfield.jpg" width="300" height="225" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/The_Kop%2C_Anfield.jpg/450px-The_Kop%2C_Anfield.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/The_Kop%2C_Anfield.jpg/600px-The_Kop%2C_Anfield.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:The_Kop,_Anfield.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Kop at <a href="Anfield" title="Anfield">Anfield</a>, the home of <a href="Liverpool_F.C." title="Liverpool F.C.">Liverpool F.C.</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Spion Kop</b> (or <b>Kop</b> for short) is a colloquial name or term for a number of <a href="Terrace_(stadium)" title="Terrace (stadium)">terraces</a> and stands at <a href="List_of_sports" title="List of sports">sports</a> <a href="Stadium" title="Stadium">stadiums</a>, particularly in the <a href="United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>. Their steep nature resembles a hill near <a href="Ladysmith,_KwaZulu-Natal" title="Ladysmith, KwaZulu-Natal">Ladysmith</a>, <a href="South_Africa" title="South Africa">South Africa</a>, that was the scene of the <a href="Battle_of_Spion_Kop" title="Battle of Spion Kop">Battle of Spion Kop</a> in January 1900 during the <a href="Second_Boer_War" title="Second Boer War">Second Boer War</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
<td>
<div id="toctitle">
